Text.Value: Ska'kek kir Gith shabell'eth. My blade rests. Mother Gith compels you to listen.

EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to Lae'zel. SKA-kek keer gith shah-BELL-eth. 'The word of Gith be present'.

Text.Value: You make a dangerous accusation. Vlaakith would call your words heresy.
Who is this 'seed of Vlaakith's demise'?
I've not come to kill you, child. I've come to aid you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Voss should not be menacing here. Turns out he's a good guy. And he should be very charismatic all through this dialogue.

Text.Value: For now, that will do.
I am neither. 'Clear of heart, clear of mind, and bound by no master.' Now - you must listen.
I've heard word from Crèche Y'llek. You are infected - yet the one in the Prism has chosen you, protects you with their power.
The queen's warriors hunt you. The qua'nith will sound out when you come near their portals. Hear its cry, and prepare for battle - or slip away.
I will not abandon my queen. Die, kith'rak!
My own queen hunts me. Why in the hells should I listen to you?
Because her throne rests on lies, more than a hundred gish scholars could count in a lifetime. I will share but two.
I've sought their freedom for aeons. When the Prism went missing, I feared the worst.
But I know the truth.
I'm not giving you the Astral Prism, if that's what you're wanting.
All that remains is the key that unchains them - and I've found someone who I believe can provide it.
Vlaakith's demise? I should run you through for suggesting it.
I am not Hshar'lak. You must hear me - Vlaakith has abandoned us.
But the one inside's chosen you as an ally, protects you with their power.
I come to aid you.
Who is the person inside the Prism?
I've not come to kill you, Lae'zel. I've come to aid you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Voss should not be menacing here. Turns out he's a good guy. And he should be very charismatic all through this dialogue.

Text.Value: Your choice is made. Hta'zith!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Voss grabs his blade from the ground and gears up to attack.

Text.Value: Child of Gith. Or should I say - Hshar'lak?
What are you asking of me, Voss?
If they have not said, they must have good reason. And I won't be the one to betray them.
A kith'rak resists the Undying Queen? That either makes you a fool - or a hero.
He's trying to corrupt you with lies - we need to get rid of him.
He's trying to corrupt you with lies - we need to get rid of him.
He's trying to corrupt you with lies - we need to get rid of him.
He's trying to corrupt you with lies - we need to get rid of him.
He's trying to corrupt you with lies - we need to get rid of him.
He's trying to corrupt you with lies - we need to get rid of him.
I do not bring her mercy. I bring you the truth.
Your words carry truth - I will meet you in Baldur's Gate.
Forgiveness? Ignorant child. In Vlaakith, there is no forgiveness. You might as well beg a dragon for its wings.
Keep the Astral Prism close. Let no one take it from you. Slay any who try.
*Ascension - the foundation of githyanki belief. Bring Queen Vlaakith an illithid's head, and she will grant you an eternal home in the great city of Tu'narath.*
No more words. This camp will be your grave.
Honoured kith'rak. Tell me you bring me Vlaakith's forgiveness.
Lae'zel - together we will break our chains, and be Vlaakith's slaves no longer.
I'll let you leave this camp alive. But I can promise nothing more.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player wakes up in the middle of the night to find Kith'rak Voss there, accompanied by one other gith. Voss holds his sword in a seemingle aggressive manner.

Text.Value: I knew you would fight - and I knew you would win. I needed to ensure Vlaakith's trust. This was the only way.
*This has been your life's purpose. Could Vlaakith truly intend to consume your life force to strengthen her own?*
At ease, child. Jhe'stil Kith'rak does not come to kill you -

EditorData.NodeContext: zhe-STILL KITH-rack. Supreme Knight. Fatherly, but not antagonsistically like before.

Text.Value: Be at ease. I bring only truth.
Lae'zel. I see T'lak'ma Ghir in you - Sister in Freedom. Together, we will be our people's light.
It is not.
That very power will be the end of Vlaakith's tyranny. The Prism's tenant must be let loose.
Take this. It is a qua'nith - a psionic detector.
The Prism's tenant alone has the power to end Vlaakith's tyranny. They must be let loose.
A fool stumbles without cause. A hero serves a cause without question.
A kith'rak. Has our Queen sent you to slay me yourself?

EditorData.logicalname: Player is meeting Voss for the first time

Text.Value: The zaith'isk does not purify - it extracts memory and kills the infected. Nor does the lich queen glorify the ascended. She feeds on most all of them to grow her power and pursue godhood.
I am no slave. It is Vlaakith who will purify me and ascend me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Thoughtful, not too vehement. zhe-STIL KITH-rack.

Text.Value: I am no servant of Queen Vlaakith. But I know who you are, and I know of the Astral Prism you carry.
I know you carry the Astral Prism, Lae'zel.
I've heard enough. Taste my fury, kith'rak.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [SCENE] Voss takes his blade from the ground and rises.

Text.Value: Instead, you've granted the opportunity I've so long awaited.
Enjoy your next breath. It will be your last.
Speak. You have my ear, as Mother Gith taught us.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [SCENE] Voss and his companions wave their hands together, and a portal opens before them. They step through and the portals close behind them.

Text.Value: Fine. I'll hear what you have to say before I gut you.
I should go. Vlaakith's gaze pierces the seas and skies. She believes me loyal - and I can't afford her mistrust.
Your cronies tried to kill us. Why should I listen to you?

EditorData.logicalname: Gith tried to kill Lae'zel before

Text.Value: Within it lies the seed of Vlaakith's demise. And I intend to help you bring it to fruition.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [SCENE] Voss kneels and lays his sword on the ground in the githyanki sign of submission.

EditorData.stateContext: Voss is kneeling, sword laid across the ground.

Text.Value: Now - to Baldur's Gate. I'll be waiting, Lae'zel.
The Prism's tenant can put an end to Vlaakith's tyranny. They must be let loose.
I'm asking for your help - and your trust.
Lies, Lae'zel - every last one. There is no purification, no ascension.
Supreme Kith'rak. Has Vlaakith sent you to slay me with your own blade?
Bring the Prism to Baldur's Gate. I'll be waiting in a taproom called Sharess' Caress. That is where we decide the fate of our people.

Synopsis: Voss arrives at camp and attempts to sway Laezel to his side after the events of the Creche.
